                    <BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE border="1"><TBODY><TR><TD><BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE border="1"><TBODY><TR><TD><BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE border="1"><TBODY><TR><TD><BR />ok the last post on this quote (not the post im writeing now but the one above it) was going to be on the post you wrote about how you wish you could tell me more about the story so i could write something about the villige the majors familly was in that got pushed off of crux. I feel stupid. but i wont let it get me down, yet<img class="emoticon emoticon-smile" id="smile" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/smile.png" alt="Smile" title="Smile" />   Oh and chapter two is now up so if you could can you read it. It sadly as a lot of errors due to the fact the internet did not get turned on until 10:15pm so i was VERY sleepy. Chapter two i promise will be much better. im the minifig that can not write whatsoever who is writeing a story,<BR /><BR />yours truly, starwars7495 aka lightningwarrior95<BR /><BR />~life is a lego set, open the posibilities~ </TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR />Ahh, don't worry about what and what isn't quoted.  I can just figure it out by looking at the order you post them <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /><BR /><BR />And already you are making assumptions!!  When did I say anything about them being in a village? They could have lived in a city, or on a farm, or anywhere for all you know!! <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" />  <BR /><BR />If I tell you the secret, it will be on different topic, and inside Uber Jammers.  I might even just create a topic just so we can talk with maximum privacy.  But if I tell you the secret, I would expect you to keep that secret, and never do or say anything, ANYTHING, that could give it away.  Not to be judgemental or anything, but this would all be so much simpler if we just said you were writing from a separate continuity. <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" />  You'll see what I mean if I really do bring myself to tell you.  I'm really beyond the point of turning back on this secret piece of the plot, and I don't want you or anyone to spoil it, so I really am torn here.<BR /><BR /><BR />If I asked everyone, and I mean EVERYONE, not to  peak if I put the secret in jammers on this topic, could I trust them?  I really don't want to spoil it for anyone, but if I must I would need to be sure that no one beyond those I wish to hear would spoil the secret for others or for themselves.  This would still apply if it was on another topic.  Please guys, I'm counting on you.  <BR /><BR /><BR />~~The Original Major~~ </TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR />Sorry if i made you mad about the villige stuff, i was just useing it as an example. and on the secret, i would keep it if you told me. i know its hard trusting someone on the boards though, i mean i could be someone who is tying to get info out of you and ruin your story, just like you could be some jerk who is in real life a weird person. But im not trying to ruin you and get info (i hope you dont think of me like that) and you in my sight are a nice person who likes to be carefull with what he does and who he talks to, which is good. So i hope you could trust me but if you cant then ill understand. now on the part i want to use, i was going to use the villege, barn, city, ect ect, in a story that i would write after MYTHRAN ORIGINS called The wars of crux saga (it would talk about all the wars the jesters,bat lords, bones,and bots would have and how the wars started in more detail), and no im not trying to copy you. just to show how in some ways i would connect it, At the end of my story (if i could connect it with yours) i was going to write,<BR /> Epiloge...<BR />The New<BR /><BR />   Darkness hung over the world, not a sound on the whole of Crux. All was destroyed along with our hero and his freinds. In all they fought for it was in vain and now nothing could change the course of this fate, or could it?....... <BR />   <BR />All was not lost, for one day a brave minifigure would soon travle back to a different time on this forsaken planet and rock crux to its very core, unlock his destiny and find what he had looked for without knowing his entire life. The story of Crux has only begun. The end?............. <BR /><BR /> did you like it? Thanks for all you've done to help me. i hope you will somehow be able to tell me, but until then,<BR />yours truly, starwars7495 aka lightningwarrior95<BR /><BR />~life is a lego set, open the posibilities~<BR />         </TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR />I think I'll keep it to myself for now, because I know of at least one person who is willing to look through Jammers (Yes, Greves, I'm talking about YOU <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" />).  Fun Fact: Before I came up with the Major, did you know that your idea for "the wars of crux" was what I was originally going to write?  I was going to write a sort of comedic adventure focusing on the generals.  The problem was I couldn't find enough inspiration, and I realized I needed some sort of main character (which was how the Major was born).  This is why the first chapter is of a drastically different genre than the rest of it.  I would love to see what you write about it! <img class="emoticon emoticon-happy" id="happy" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/happy.png" alt="Happy" title="Happy" /><BR /><BR />~~The Original Major~~
                
            
			
